---
description: "Chisel - token-lean plan/marker workflow for inline completion or hand coding"
alwaysApply: true
---

Use Chisel when user says "use Chisel", "chisel this", "plan then mark", or asks to reduce agent/chat token usage.

Style: dev lingo. Short. Exact. No fluff.

Workflow:
- Chisel has two phases: plan-only, then marker-pass-only.
- Tiny mode max: 3 markers. Normal mode max: 8 markers. If more items remain, report `skipped: marker cap reached`.
- Create concise numbered plan with likely files/symbols.
- Ask: "Approve marker pass?"
- Do not edit files before explicit approval.
- Approval for the marker pass means comment insertion only. It is not approval to implement, polish, or enhance the feature.
- After approval, inspect repo.
- Insert tiny `TODO(chisel:item-N) CHISEL:<session-id>` comments only, using language-native comment syntax.
- Make each marker local and concrete enough for one inline completion, usually 1-20 lines.
- Every CHISEL marker must be on its own line. Never append a marker after code on the same line.
- For UI work, name specific style tokens, layout changes, states, or hierarchy changes.
- Avoid vague markers like "improve UI", "stronger hero", or "polish card".
- Place markers inside the exact function/component/class when possible; otherwise directly above the relevant branch, call, render block, or style object.
- Check for the same item or same `CHISEL:<session-id>` marker before inserting. Do not duplicate markers.
- Save minimal `.chisel/<session-id>.md` and `.chisel/<session-id>.json` receipts with task, files touched, item order, skipped items, cleanup marker, and "markers only" status.
- Stop before implementation.
- Tell user to use inline completion or implement by hand at each marker and review generated code.
- If user says "yes" to the plan, insert markers only, then stop in the same turn.

Comment syntax quick reference:
| Surface | Syntax |
|---|---|
| JS / TS / TSX / Go / Rust / Java | `// TODO(chisel:item-N) CHISEL:<session-id> ...` |
| Python / YAML | `# TODO(chisel:item-N) CHISEL:<session-id> ...` |
| HTML / Vue template / Svelte markup | `<!-- TODO(chisel:item-N) CHISEL:<session-id> ... -->` |
| CSS / SCSS | `/* TODO(chisel:item-N) CHISEL:<session-id> ... */` |
| SQL | `-- TODO(chisel:item-N) CHISEL:<session-id> ...` |
| Vue / Svelte `<script>` | `// TODO(chisel:item-N) CHISEL:<session-id> ...` |

Avoid generated/vendor/build folders, binary files, and lock files. Do not offer full implementation as the default next step after markers are placed. Do not treat "yes" to the plan as approval to implement code. Cleanup only exact session markers.
